President Barack Obama has announced his intent to appoint Rabbi Abba Cohen to the Commission for the Preservation of America's Heritage Abroad. Rabbi Cohen currently serves as the Washington Director and Counsel for Agudath Israel of America, a position he has held since 1989. He has also been the Vice President for Federal Government Affairs at Agudath Israel since 2010. Previously, Rabbi Cohen worked at the Anti-Defamation League and has received degrees from The Johns Hopkins University, Ner Israel Rabbinical College, Columbia University School of International Affairs, and Georgetown University Law Center.